foia:ReliedUponStatute.foia:ReliedUponStatuteInformationWithhel: Confidential Returns and Return Information: 26 USC § 6103 prohibits the disclosure of (1) tax returns and return information of third party taxpayers (section 6103(a)); (2) the standards used for selection of returns for examination (section 6103(b)(2)); and (3) a requester’s own return information if the release would seriously impair federal tax administration (section 6103(e)(7)).
